<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR LOCAL TEAMS GAIN USTA FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Four Orange County teams won section titles at the United States Tennis Assn. 
championships here Sunday at Los Caballeros Sports Village. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Caballeros Sports Village team won the men's open division by 
defeating the West End Club of Tennis, 2-1. Hollywood Returning Retirees of 
Irvine beat the Bakersfield Country Club, 2-1, for the women's open title. 
</P>
<P>
 The teams advance to the USTA League championships Sept. 29 to Oct. 2 in Las 
Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Teams from Los Caballeros won the men's and women's 4.0 divisions and advance 
to the USTA championships Oct. 6-9 in Tucson. 
</P>
