<P>
PEOPLE: MCCRAW NAMED PUBLISHER OF LOS ANGELES MAGAZINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joan McCraw has been named president and publisher of Los Angeles Magazine 
which is owned by Capital Cities/ABC Inc., New York.She was formerly vice 
president of advertising for National Geographic. McGraw succeeds Geoff Miller 
as publisher. Miller, a founder and former editor of the magazine, announced in 
April that he planned to retire after 34 years with the magazine. 
