<P>
MINDY POMPER RECEIVES DEAN FILM GRANT AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Roy W. Dean Film Grant Award was presented to Mindy Pomper for 
"Trailblazers: Unsung Military Heroines of World War II" on Aug. 11 during 
ceremonies held at the Directors Guild of America. The $15,000 prize is awarded 
to aspiring documentary filmmakers, and the winner and four finalists were 
chosen from more than 7,000 submissions. The four finalists included: Arledge 
Armenaki for "The Big Struggle," Zelmer Bothic for "People United," Pamela 
Beere Briggs for "Women of Mystery" and Julia McCamy Tell for "What Is God?" 
</P>
