World War II. 
</P>
<P>
 The Nazis gave our boys the opportunity for an all-expenses-paid trip to see 
Europe close up, from Omaha Beach to climbing up the steep hills of Italy and 
participating at the exciting Battle of the Bulge. 
</P>
<P>
 And the European Catholics had even more fun killing each other all over 
Europe. As a special boon, German Catholics and Lutherans got an 
all-expense-paid tour of neighboring Catholic countries and a winter vacation 
in Russia. Who can forget that! 
</P>
<P>
 Of course, who can forget those nasty German Catholic students and their 
priest who let it be known they had profound disagreements with the Nazis. 
Then, too, there was a distinguished German theologian who also disagreed. The 
adults were hung with a narrow cord and the students beheaded. The Nazis 
certainly knew how to handle those miscreants. 
</P>
<P>
 Yes. Now is just the right time for Catholics everywhere to celebrate the 
likes of Waldheim. How easily we forget what the Nazis did. 
</P>
