<P>
FERRY CAPTAIN LOADED RICE ON CROWDED BOAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A ferry captain loaded hundreds of bags of rice on an already crowded boat 
shortly before it sank, survivors said Sunday.About 350 people were missing and 
feared dead in the disaster. 
</P>
<P>
 Passenger Abdul Khaleque said the extra weight of the rice caused the ship to 
overturn. 
</P>
<P>
 The double-decker ferry was carrying about 410 passengers, double its 
authorized load, when it capsized and sank Saturday near Chandpur, 40 miles 
south of Dhaka. 
</P>
<P>
 About 60 people were rescued. 
</P>
