</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Treasury Offers Contracts: The Treasury Department, its bureaus and several 
prime contractors will participate Tuesday and Wednesday in an unusual 
procurement conference for small and minority- and women-owned businesses.More 
than $2 million in contracts will be available for on-the-spot bidding. Bidding 
results for many small contracts will be announced each hour and for larger 
contracts within 10 days of the Partnerships '94 conference, which will be held 
at the Los Angeles Convention Center. Registration is $30 per person. The 
department suggests that each company be represented by several employees 
supplied with cellular telephones, calculators, phone numbers of suppliers and 
distributors, and a rubber stamp with the company's name and address. For more 
information, call (800) 871-2897. 
