<P>
 Savoy, Forte Hotel Groups to Combine Management: Savoy Hotel and Forte, the 
British-based rivals that run some of the world's finest hotels, have agreed on 
a joint venture, London's Independent newspaper reported.It said that 
management of all the Savoy hotels -- including the Connaught and Claridges in 
London and the Lancaster in Paris -- and of some or all of Forte's luxury-class 
hotels will be combined. Three key trusts that hold about 40% of Savoy's voting 
rights reportedly forged the agreement with Forte, which is based on a plan 
offered by Morgan Stanley Bank. Since Forte's unsuccessful attempt to take 
control of Savoy in the late 1980s, Forte has held 42.1% of the voting rights. 
