PACIFIC WATCH: CHINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Inflation Rate Inches Upward: China's inflation rate rose to 21.4% in July 
from 20% in June, according to retail price index figures from the State 
Statistics Bureau, the official China Daily reported.The newspaper said 
officials blamed the rising prices on sharply increased investment in fixed 
assets such as plant and equipment by state-owned enterprises. Investment in 
fixed assets rose 72.9% in the year to July, compared to 43.5% in the year to 
June. China is seeking to reduce its inflation rate to 13% by the end of the 
year. 
</P>
