<TEXT>
<P>
 Some Chinese Businessmen to Be Invited: Taiwan has decided in principle to 
allow businessmen from China to visit, to curb abuses of permits intended for 
cultural and academic trips, a senior government official said. The move came a 
day after the Cabinet approved a Communications Ministry request for a study of 
technical problems involved in direct transport links with China.Officials said 
that approval did not herald a change in a longstanding government ban on 
direct relations between Taiwan and the mainland. The preliminary decision by 
officials of the Mainland Affairs Council (MAC), which handles official policy 
