<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BREA; APARTMENT UNITS FOR SENIORS OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has tentatively approved zoning changes and an amendment to 
Brea's land-use plan to allow construction of a 108-unit apartment complex for 
senior citizens. The project is proposed for a two-acre site on North Brea 
Boulevard near West Central Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The vote last week was 4 to 0 in favor of the project. Councilman Burnie 
Dunlap abstained because he is the director of insurance services at Brea 
Community Hospital, which is near the proposed apartment site. 
</P>
<P>
 Some of the council members expressed concern that only 84 parking spaces are 
planned for the complex. A survey of senior apartment complexes in the area 
indicated that the amount of parking was adequate, however. 
</P>
<P>
 Final approval of the project is expected to be considered at the next council 
meeting on Sept. 6. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
