<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH KILLED IN FREEWAY CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 15-year-old boy was killed in a crash on the Riverside Freeway early Sunday 
after the car in which he was riding was struck from behind by another car, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The youth was identified as John Dilag of Lawndale, said Senior Deputy Coroner 
Larry Esslinger. 
</P>
<P>
 Dilag and three others in the car driven by a 17-year-old Torrance resident 
were eastbound on the freeway east of Gypsum Canyon Road when the accident 
occurred at 12:39 a.m., said CHP dispatcher Deborah Peake. 
</P>
<P>
 The car in which Dilag was a passenger ran off the road and struck a guardrail 
on the right shoulder, Peake said. 
</P>
<P>
 The CHP released no other information on the incident Sunday. 
</P>
