<P>
MAN FOUND DEAD AFTER SHOTS FIRED AT BAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old man was found early Sunday lying in a street with a gunshot to 
the head just minutes after he and other men fled from a shootout at a local 
bar, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The dead man was identified as Candelario Quiroz Sosa of Pacoima.Quiroz Sosa 
had been one of the occupants of a van that had been driven away from the Maeba 
Bar in the 13500 block of Van Nuys Boulevard in Pacoima, said Police Sgt. 
Michelle Daniels. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers responded to a call at the bar about 12:15 a.m., and were later 
informed that a van that left the bar was found in San Fernando, Daniels said. 
</P>
<P>
 Less than 15 minutes after the incident, a San Fernando police officer found 
Quiroz Sosa's body and the van on Truman Avenue near the intersection of Brand 
Boulevard when the officer responded to a resident's report of an apparent 
hit-and-run accident, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles police arrived at the scene and took over the investigation, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sosa was taken by ambulance to a local hospital where he died, Daniels said. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday, police were trying to unravel the crime to determine whether Sosa 
and the men he was with were involved in the shooting at the bar. 
</P>
<P>
 "There was a shooting at the bar, yes, but we don't know yet if they are 
suspects or witnesses," said one detective working on the case. 
</P>
